solution: ```class Solution {
    public int countOperations(int num1, int num2) {
        int ops = 0;
        while (num1 != 0 && num2 != 0) {
            if (num1 >= num2) {
                num1 -= num2;
            } else {
                num2 -= num1;
            }
            ops++;
        }
        return ops;
    }
}```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log(min(num1, num2)))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Uses the Euclidean algorithm's subtraction pattern, which converges quickly; avoids recursion and extra memory, making it both fast and energy-efficient.

